version 1.99 - Kurt Granroth <granroth@suse.com>
- Ported aKtion! to KDE 2.0
- Converted aKtion! to embedded component

version 0.3.6
-added Italian translation (thanks to Alberto Scattini <sigmund@stud.unipg.it>)
-updated french and slovak translations.
-now the player exits from full-screen mode when the video is stopped
-fixed a (stupid) bug in full-screen mode (when using XFree-VidMode extensions)
 that caused some core-dumps. Fixed documentation too.
-you don't need to be the root user to use the XF86-VidMode extensions.
-changed mime-type filenames (be sure to remove the old ones,
 doing a 'make uninstall' before installing the new aKtion version!)
 Recommended by Troy Engel.

version 0.3.5
-added XFree86-VidMode Extensions support
 Most of the code was shamelessly stealed from the SDL library ( http://www.devolution.com/~slouken/SDL )
 Read the documentation for more info (in the "Full Screen Mode" section)
-bugfixes

version 0.3.4
-updated french translation, and added slovak translation

version 0.3.3
-added DND support
 (thanks to Fernando Herrera <fherrera@eurielec.etsit.upm.es>)
-fixed full-screen mode for KDE 1.1
-fixed xanim 2.8.0 compatibility 
-added frame capture function
-configurable xanim executable

version 0.3.2
-Full screen mode added
-Configuration window redesigned
-bugfixes

version 0.3.1
-bugfixes only

version 0.3.0
-resizing "on the fly" allowed
-mimetypes bug fix

